%b%O%b allows Operators/Administrators with access, to
maintain control on the network.
For more information on the commands, type
%b/msg %O HELP <command>%b

    HELP       Display this screen
    IDENTIFY   Identify with %O with your password
%+o%b* * * *
%+o%bOperator commands:%b
%+o    CLONES     Display list of clones on the network
%+g    GLINE      Prevent a user from joining the network 
%+g    KLINE      Kline a user, if your ircd supports it
%+o    HTM        Toggle HTM on/off
%+o    HUB        Display a hub's leaf servers
%+j    JUPE       Prevent a server from connecting
%+o    KILL       Disconnect a user from the network
%+o    STATS      Display various statistics
%+o    STATUS     Display current status
%+o    UMODE      Set various usermodes for yourself
%+g    UNGLINE    Remove a gline
%+j    UNJUPE     Remove a jupe on a server
%+a%b* * * *
%+a%bAdministrator commands:%b
%+a    CHANNEL    Display channels matching a pattern
%+a    IGNORE     Prevent a user from using services
%+a    JOIN       Monitor a channel
%+a    JUMP       Switch hub servers
%+a    KILLCHAN   Kill users in a channel
%+a    KILLHOST   Kill users matching a certain host
%+s    OMODE      Set modes on any channel
%+a    PART       Stop monitoring a channel
%+a    SECURE     Secure a channel
%+a    TRACE      Display users matching a pattern
%+s%b* * * *
%+s%bServices Administrator commands:%b
%+s    DIE        Shutdown services
%+s    DUMP       Send raw data to hub server
%+s    OFF/ON     (De)activate services
%+s    REHASH     Reload configuration file
%+s    RELOAD     Reload nickname/channel/memo/stat databases
%+s    RESTART    Restart services
%+s    SAVE       Save nick/chan/memo/stat/oper databases
%+s    SET        Set configuration options at runtime
